&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;code&gt;useDebounce&lt;/code&gt; for search inputs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;code&gt;useAuth&lt;/code&gt; for login/session handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;code&gt;usePrevious&lt;/code&gt; for tracking previous values&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;code&gt;useDarkMode&lt;/code&gt; for theme toggling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;code&gt;useOnlineStatus&lt;/code&gt; to detect internet connectivity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


Conclusion
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Custom hooks unlock one of React‚Äôs greatest strengths: the ability to share logic cleanly and efficiently. They help you build scalable apps, reduce repetition, and keep components focused on UI‚Äînot complexity.&lt;br&gt;
Today‚Äôs topic might feel small, but mastering custom hooks will make a huge difference as your projects grow.&lt;/p&gt;

